comments.body:
Hi @ardakuyumcu / @rhatdan,

I've created a auth.json in /etc/containers/ directory but it is not working defaultly login to buildah login quay.io reqgistry.
I  gone through some tutorials and found that we have to create auth.json at **${XDG_RUNTIME_DIR}/containers/auth.json**  dir.

Can you please help how, what and where to set ${XDG_RUNTIME_DIR} value of this? I have requirement when user got access to container, he  by default login to quay.io registry or some other private OCR registry.

Im using below auth.json file.

{
   "auths": {
		"quay.io": {
			 "auth": "base64 encoded cred"
		}
   }
}

using below commands in Dockerfile

COPY auth.json /etc/containers/

RUN chmod -R 777 /etc/containers/auth.json
